pddl.prompt:
You are the orchestrator. Integrate the availability reports from the participants to produce a PDDL model that finds a 60-minute meeting slot that is free for Billy, Maria and William on Monday between 09:00 and 17:00, using the environment granularity.
Inputs (participant availabilities):
{avail_billy}
{avail_maria}
{avail_william}
Environment public information:
{environment->public_information}
Orchestrator goal:
{agents->orchestrator->goal}
Requirements:
- Create predicates, objects and actions needed to model time slots and participant occupancy.
- The PDDL problem must encode the meeting duration (60 minutes) and the participants' constraints so that any solution corresponds to a valid meeting start time.
- Target the FastDownwards solver; ensure the PDDL is standard STRIPS/PDDL 2.1 compatible.
- Enclose the PDDL domain between <domain></domain> tags and the PDDL problem between <problem></problem> tags.
Think step by step and provide the final PDDL domain and problem.
